properties.Title: Extreme Cold Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: The coldest wind chill values will be between minus 50 and minus 55. Wind chill values will dip to near -50 early this morning under a clear, cold airmass and wind up to 15 km/h. Wind chill values will rise above -50 by mid-morning as the temperature rises. ### Risks are greater for young children, older adults, people with chronic illnesses, people working or exercising outdoors, and those without proper shelter. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. properties.Title: Ontario Amber Alert
properties.Summary:
Description: Toronto Police Service have requested an AMBER Alert broadcast in relation to an abducted child. The victim, Shammah Jolayemi, is described as male, 14 years old, 6 feet 0 inches,140 lbs, brown eyes, black short hair, wearing grey shirt with hood, track pants with orange stripes, Air Jordan (black/yellow) shoes, black shiny, puffy winter jacket. Two unknown suspects both wearing black jackets and bandanas on head, 18 to 22 years old. Vehicle is Newer Model Black Jeep Wrangler with tinted windows and fog lights on bush bar. Vehicle was last seen near 353 Driftwood Avenue, North York.

properties.Title: Blizzard Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Blizzard conditions with gusty winds and visibility frequently near zero in snow and blowing snow are expected or occurring. An arctic ridge over Yukon has generated very strong northerly winds with gusts up to 90 km/h near White Pass. Strong winds combined with freshly fallen snow will lead to visibilities frequently below 400 metres across the South Klondike Highway today. Blizzard conditions will begin to improve this evening over most of the highway while White Pass will continue to see reduced visibilities until late tonight. ### Travel is expected to be extremely hazardous due to reduced visibility. Road closures are possible. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather in British Columbia or Yukon, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or YTstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm or #YTStorm.

properties.Title: Wind Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Strong winds that may cause damage are expected or occurring. A frontal system will continue to generate strong winds to Haida Gwaii and the North Coast this morning. Southeast winds of 80 to 100 km/h will continue along the coastal sections of the North Coast then shift to southwest winds of 50 to 70 km/h later this morning. For Haida Gwaii, southwest winds of 50 to 70 km/h will continue with some areas potentially receiving southwest winds of 90 km/h. These winds will diminish this afternoon. ### Wind warnings are issued when there is a significant risk of damaging winds. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm.

properties.Title: Blowing Snow Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Poor visibility in snow and blowing snow is expected or occurring in some locations. Further snowfall: 2 cm. Maximum wind gusts: northerly between 60 and 80 km/h. Locations: Rigolet and vicinity and Hopedale and vicinity. Time span: continuing until Friday morning for Hopedale and vicinity, and until this evening elsewhere. Remarks: Snow will taper to flurries tonight. Strong northerly winds will accompany the snow, reducing visibility in blowing snow. ### Visibility may be significantly and suddenly reduced to near zero. Blowing snow advisories are issued when winds are expected to create blowing snow giving poor visibility to 800 metres or less for at least 3 hours. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.
